Program req.
mouse
super VGA
CPU 286 or greater
The program is mouse driven but keyboard input is accepted for
most commands.
The program card shuffle has been written to be as random as a
physical manipulation of real cards would be.
A review screen has been incorporated to allow the player to
analyze the statistics of the game.

The player can select the number of decks for the shoe - 1 to 6
Bet advice is available at players choice.

To begin the game just type "BJAC"
Select the number of decks to be played
Place bets using the calculator pad
On the calculator pad are the following commands:
"A" - If "A" is selected that hand will be played by the computer
using accepted hit/stand/double/split
     logic.
"V"  If "V" is selected that table position will be left vacant
(No Hand Played)
"C"  If "C" is selected the entered bet amount will be cleared
form the display.
"Enter"   The standard broken arrow symbol represents the enter
key - Select to Place bet on the table.

Note: When a player response is required for a hit or stand you
may use the enter key for "Hit" and the 
spacebar for "Stand".

Enjoy!!!